STEPS:
1. Web template(html, css, javascript)
2. create react app

When creating a server
npm init
install express
create server.js file
move data.js 
install dep using " npm install @babel/cli @babel/core @babel/node @babel/preset-env nodemon --save-dev"
because current express runs on es5
"--save-dev" flag required to save dep in the right object i package.json file
run server command "node file.js" eg "node backend/server.js"
change script object test to "start" : "nodemon --watch backend --exec babel-node backend/server.js"
so that npm start in the server will access and run the server file as well
create hook in component for fetching data from api
backend server should be running before api requests can be made

manage state redux